<div type="definition">
<p>DISTRESS CAUSED by a BAD SITUATION in one's BODY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The clearly dominant general word for physical pain is tòng 痛 (ant. shū 舒 "feel well" and wú yàng 無恙 "fail nothing").</p>
<p>NB: Curiously, it is hard to think of other common words for pain. Téng 疼 is post-Buddhist.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>疼痛 is probably the most general and abstract modern word for any kind of pain.</p>
<p>苦痛</p>
<p>痛苦</p>
<p>傷痛</p>
<p>苦楚</p>
<p>痛楚</p>
<p>酸楚</p>
<p>苦處</p>
<p>痛處</p>
<p>苦頭</p>
<p>苦難</p>
<p>苦水</p>
<p>苦</p>
<p>切膚之痛</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
